result.execSummary:
Dena S. Baker was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Dena S. Baker was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Dena S. Baker

records.addlTxt:
[ma] Case called at 10:41 AM 
Defendant Dena S. Baker not in court.  Michael C. Witt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

The Court reviews the court record. 

Per information received from the jail, Ms. Baker was picked up by Missouri on 6/10/22

The Court closes case and takes no further action.
recess: 10:44am

Extradition Commitment Warrant

ec/pc: DA, JCJ, Governor (6/2/22--ma)

[ma] Case called at 1:42pm 
Defendant Dena S. Baker appears via videoconferencing from the Jefferson County Jail, in custody, along with Public Defender Cassi Nelson, as a friend of the court, Ms. Baker has refused to be evaluated.  Public Service Special Prosecutor Melanie Flint appears for the State of Wisconsin. 

The Court finds that the video-connection is sight and sound sufficient. 

Service of Complaint admitted, reading waived.

The Court verifies that Atty Nelson has reviewed with Ms. Baker her rights.

recess 1:45pm---reconvene: 1:55pm 
Defendant Dena S. Baker appears in court, in custody. Public Service Special Prosecutor Melanie Flint appears for the State of Wisconsin. 
The Court verifies date of birth and address.

The Court finds based on colloquy with Ms. Baker that the Defendant for the MO case is the same one that appears in courtroom. 
The Court finds that the defendant has been accused of a crime in the requesting state.
The Court finds that Ms. Baker has waived her right to counsel and extradition hearing. 

The Court commits Ms. Baker to Jefferson County Jail, not to exceed 30 days, to allow MO to get her. 

recess: 2:02pm 
NEXT: Hearing on 6/21/22 at 9:30am (Has MO picked up Ms. Baker?)
